      "content": "Originalism is a judicial philosophy that argues the Constitution should be interpreted based on the original understanding of its authors and the people at the time it was ratified. The main legal justification for originalism is that it preserves the Constitution as a stable and enduring document, preventing judges from imposing their personal values and preferences on the law. Originalists believe that the framers' intent should guide legal decisions, ensuring that the Constitution remains a reflection of the will of the people, not the whims of contemporary judges. This approach is seen as a way to maintain the rule of law and prevent judicial activism.",
